What is EFS?
Elastic File System: 

EC2 : EBS hard disk you can attach multiple EBS to sinlge instance but not multiple
EC2: EFS file sharing can share to multiple instances 


EFS managed shared file storage service
It allows multiple servers (EC2 instances)
It works like a network shared drive in the Cloud
It deals NFS protocol

Real-Time Example:
-------------------
Imagine:
1. 3 applications servers running in autoscaling
2. All servers need access to:
  upoaded images
  logs
  shared configuration files
  website content

Instead of storing files separately on each server, all servers connect to one shared storage.

Key Features:
-------------
1. Fully managed (handles maintenance and scaling)
2. shared storage (multiple EC2s can access same files)
3.Linux files system uses NFS protocol (Network File System)
4.All instances read files, write files, update files

